    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You should be aware that <code>[^a-zA-Z]</code> will replace characters not being itself in the character range A-Z/a-z. That means special characters like <code>é</code>, <code>ß</code> etc. or cyrillic characters and such will be removed. </p>\n\n<p>If the replacement of these characters is not wanted use pre-defined character classes  instead:</p>\n\n<pre><code> str.replaceAll(\"[^\\\\p{IsAlphabetic}\\\\p{IsDigit}]\", \"\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>PS: <code>\\p{Alnum}</code> does not achieve this effect, it acts the same as <code>[A-Za-z0-9]</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "user_type" : "does_not_exist",
      "display_name" : "user5004526"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1478028997,
    "creation_date" : 1478028997,
    "answer_id" : 40367397,
    "question_id" : 1805518,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Simple method:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public boolean isBlank(String value) {\n    return (value == null || value.equals(\"\") || value.equals(\"null\") || value.trim().equals(\"\"));\n}\n\npublic String normalizeOnlyLettersNumbers(String str) {\n    if (!isBlank(str)) {\n        return str.replaceAll(\"[^\\\\p{L}\\\\p{Nd}]+\", \"\");\n    } else {\n        return \"\";\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11324616,
      "reputation" : 11,
      "user_id" : 8303977,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/83e675a16c0c982612ccf6452cedba01?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Albin",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8303977/albin"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1503503190,
    "last_edit_date" : 1503503190,
    "creation_date" : 1503501711,
    "answer_id" : 45843707,
    "question_id" : 1805518,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>public static void main(String[] args) {\n    String value = \" Chlamydia_spp. IgG, IgM &amp; IgA Abs (8006) \";\n\n    System.out.println(value.replaceAll(\"[^A-Za-z0-9]\", \"\"));\n\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>output: <strong>ChlamydiasppIgGIgMIgAAbs8006</strong></p>\n\n<p>Github: <a href=\"https://github.com/AlbinViju/Learning/blob/master/StripNonAlphaNumericFromString.java\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://github.com/AlbinViju/Learning/blob/master/StripNonAlphaNumericFromString.java</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11719268,
      "reputation" : 2005,
      "user_id" : 8578684,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ea58bdbaa27987e01887b7ace77ed9c4?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "snap",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8578684/snap"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1527157132,
    "creation_date" : 1527157132,
    "answer_id" : 50506783,
    "question_id" : 1805518,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you want to also allow alphanumeric characters which don't belong to the ascii characters set, like for instance german umlaut's, you can consider using the following solution:</p>\n\n<pre><code> String value = \"your value\";\n\n // this could be placed as a static final constant, so the compiling is only done once\n Pattern pattern = Pattern.compile(\"[^\\\\w]\", Pattern.UNICODE_CHARACTER_CLASS);\n\n value = pattern.matcher(value).replaceAll(\"\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Please note that the usage of the UNICODE_CHARACTER_CLASS flag could have an impose on performance penalty (see javadoc of this flag)</p>\n"
  }, {
